This is a comprehensive ambulatory EHR certification profile. WordPress page (PHP/8.2.18, Cloudflare CDN). No redirects.\n\n### Step 2: Fetch and examine the page\n\n```bash\ncurl -sL \"https://allegiancemd.com/ehi-export-documentation\" \\\n  -H 'User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0' -o /tmp/allegiancemd-ehi.html\n```\n\nThe WordPress page uses the Divi Builder (`et_pb_*` shortcodes) which renders via JavaScript. Page content (37 KB HTML, mostly Divi boilerplate with ~2.4 KB of actual content).\n\nThe page says:\n\n> **EHI Export Documentation**\n>\n> **Introduction**\n>\n> Data is exported in [CBOR](https://cbor.io/) format (Concise Binary Object Representation) RFC 8949. The Concise Binary Object Representation (CBOR) is an open data format whose design goals include the possibility of extremely small code size, fairly small message size, and extensibility without the need for version negotiation. It offers best result and avoid formatting issues that can exist in JSON.\n>\n> Please refer to https://cbor.io/impls.html for opensource tools and examples for the creation of quick scripts.\n>\n> [Please click here](https://allegiancemd.com/ehi-export/) to see detailed data structure of the objects. Documents and Clinical data will be included in the zip file. Each document has the corresponding .meta file that describes each document.\n\n### Step 3: Follow the data structure link\n\n```bash\ncurl -sL \"https://allegiancemd.com/ehi-export/\" \\\n  -H 'User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0' -o /tmp/allegiancemd-ehi-export.html\n```\n\nResult: HTTP 200, `Content-Type: text/html`. Also extracted a structured JSON data dictionary from all pages.\n\n## What Was Found\n\n### Export Format\n\nAllegianceMD exports EHI data in **CBOR format** (Concise Binary Object Representation, RFC 8949).
